title: Driver cut free after road crash
text:
0 comments 
A DRIVER of a Subaru has had to be cut free following a road crash. 
The incident, which occurred on Warsash Road near Locks Heath at 10.45am, also involved a black Ford Focus. 
Both vehicles ended up spinning off the road due to the impact. 
The green Subaru Estate had to have its roof cut off to free the driver. Share article 
Three people, including a 75 year-old man, were taken to hospital because of their injuries. 
Five fire engines and an air ambulance were called to the scene, with the vehicles currently awaiting recovery. Promoted Stories Driver cut free after road crash in Locks Heath   Keep in touch with local news
